                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169 Bogotá: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-29T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 29, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>583. From FEA, for La Spina.<note n="66" xml:id="d787fn66">Albert F. La Spina,
                        field representative of the Foreign Economic Administration and special
                        assistant to the Ambassador in Colombia.</note> Suggest Embassy and
                    Certifying Agency continue processing Import Recommendations as heretofore as
                    approved ones will receive due consideration even if positive list which is not
                    yet ready for consideration is made effective July 1. This answers A–320, April
                    8 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>]. [FEA.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
